Lambdas containing only one statement should not nest this statement in a block
There are two ways to write lambdas that contain single statement, but one is definitely more compact and readable than the other. Note that this rule is automatically disabled when the projectâ€™s sonar.java.source is lower than 8. 
### Noncompliant
x -> {System.out.println(x+1);}
(a, b) -> { return a+b; }
### Compliant
x -> System.out.println(x+1)
(a, b) -> a+b    //For return statement, the return keyword should also be dropped
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
